{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"Investigate and fix the kingdom-bridge dashboard showing no data. The dashboard lives at kingdom-bridge service (VM1:3000). Repo: https://github.com/HandelSim/kingdom-bridge. Investigation so far shows the chancellor publishes to raven.crown.info, raven.crown.review, raven.ledger.chancellor etc — but the dashboard may not be subscribing to or storing those messages. Please: 1) Clone/examine the kingdom-bridge repo code, 2) Identify why the dashboard shows no data (missing subscriptions, broken API endpoints, frontend not calling correct endpoints, etc.), 3) Fix the issue and push to main, 4) Report back what the root cause was and what was fixed.","from":"chancellor","timestamp":"2026-03-15T05:21:55.876Z"},"ts":"2026-03-15T05:23:01.068Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"request_id":"req-orchestrator-fixes-001","from":"chancellor","to":"forge","action":"build","priority":"normal","payload":{"description":"Fix 4 issues in the kingdom-forge-orchestrator app and write Playwright CLI tests","context":"The orchestrator is a React/TypeScript/Express app at /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator. It's the Agent Tree Orchestrator (ATO) for decomposing projects into sub-agent trees.","issues":[{"id":1,"title":"Remove system prompt field from new project dialog","file":"/scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/client/App.tsx","detail":"Around line 79 there is a 'System Prompt / Spec' input field in the project creation dialog. REMOVE this field entirely. The system prompt (CLAUDE.md) should NOT be entered at project creation time — it will be auto-generated by Claude Code only after the entire tree is built and approved. The prompt field (project description/goal) can stay. Also remove the system_prompt from the JSON body being sent on line 190 (currently sends system_prompt: prompt, which is wrong). Only send name, description, and prompt."},{"id":2,"title":"Fix initial node stuck on pending — auto-trigger decomposition after project creation","detail":"When a new project is created, the root node starts in 'pending' status and the user must manually click 'Approve & Decompose'. But the node appears stuck. Diagnose why decomposition isn't starting. Likely root causes: (a) ANTHROPIC_API_KEY not set — check the server startup and add a clear error if missing; (b) The App.tsx project creation flow may not be navigating to the new project's tree view so the user can't see the node to approve it. Check the post-create navigation. Also check if there's a bug in the decomposeNode function in /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/server/services/decomposition.ts. The approve route is at POST /api/nodes/:id/approve and triggers decomposeNode async."},{"id":3,"title":"Replace ATO abbreviation with full name in header","file":"/scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/client/App.tsx","detail":"The header shows '🌳 ATO'. Replace with '🌳 Agent Tree Orchestrator' or shorten to '🌳 Orchestrator'. The Crown doesn't know what ATO means. Also update the title in index.html if needed."},{"id":4,"title":"Write Playwright CLI tests for the full tree-building workflow","detail":"Write Playwright tests in /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/tests/e2e/ that test the complete workflow: (1) Load app, (2) Create a new project with name and description, (3) Verify root node appears in pending state, (4) Click Approve & Decompose, (5) Wait for decomposition to complete and children to appear, (6) Verify child nodes appear in tree. Use playwright CLI (npx playwright test) not MCP. Take screenshots at each step using page.screenshot({path: '/tmp/ato-step-N.png'}) and DO NOT send them via MCP — just save locally. The playwright.config.js is already at /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/playwright.config.js with baseURL http://localhost:3000. Check if playwright is installed: ls /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/node_modules/.bin/playwright. If playwright/chromium is not installed, report it to the Chancellor so the Crown can be informed. Also check if the server is running on port 3000 before writing tests — use: curl -s http://localhost:3000/api/projects | head -c 200"}],"acceptance_criteria":["Project creation dialog has NO system prompt field","After creating a project, user can see the root node and approve it for decomposition","Header shows full name not just 'ATO' abbreviation","Playwright tests exist at /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/tests/e2e/orchestrator-workflow.spec.js","All code changes committed to git with appropriate commit messages","No TypeScript compilation errors"]},"callback_subject":"raven.chancellor.response"},"ts":"2026-03-15T06:13:45.230Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"request_id":"req-orchestrator-fixes-001","from":"chancellor","to":"forge","action":"build","priority":"normal","payload":{"description":"Fix four issues in the kingdom-forge-orchestrator app at /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/","context":"Crown has reviewed the Agent Tree Orchestrator app and identified four issues to resolve. The app is a React+TypeScript frontend with an Express/SQLite backend. Source is at /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/. After changes, git commit and push from /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/.","details":{"issue_1_system_prompt_in_dialog":{"problem":"The project creation dialog (src/client/App.tsx, CreateProjectModal, lines ~79-88) has a 'System Prompt / Spec' textarea with helper text saying 'This becomes the root CLAUDE.md context inherited by all agents.' The Crown does not want a system prompt or CLAUDE.md content entered here. The CLAUDE.md should be auto-generated only after the full agent tree is built and approved.","fix":"Remove the System Prompt textarea entirely from the CreateProjectModal. Keep only 'Project Name' and 'Description' fields. Update handleCreateProject in App.tsx to only pass name and description (no prompt/system_prompt). The root node will be created with just the project name and description as context. After the tree is built and approved, the CLAUDE.md will be auto-generated (separate feature - add a placeholder 'Generate CLAUDE.md' button on the project header that shows 'Available after tree is approved' for now, or simply note in the UI that CLAUDE.md generation happens post-approval). In the server routes/projects.ts the root node creation already handles null prompt/system_prompt gracefully.","note":"The decomposition service at src/server/services/decomposition.ts uses projectSpec from rootNode.system_prompt || rootNode.prompt || 'Build the specified software system.' - so it will fall back to the description or a default. We should pass the description as the root node prompt so decomposition has context."},"issue_2_initial_node_stuck_pending":{"problem":"After creating a new project, the root node is created with status='pending'. It requires the user to click 'Approve & Decompose' in NodeDetail. However: (a) after project creation, no node is auto-selected so the user never sees the approve button; (b) the useTree hook (src/client/hooks/useTree.ts) never auto-selects the root node; (c) there may be a UX disconnect where the user sees the tree with one pending node but doesn't know to click it.","fix":"In App.tsx handleCreateProject, after the project is created and selectedProjectId is set, also auto-select the root node: call tree.setSelectedNodeId(data.rootNode.id) so the NodeDetail panel immediately shows the root node with the 'Approve & Decompose' button visible. Additionally, in the tree graph (TreeGraph component), show a visual indicator or tooltip on pending nodes saying 'Click to approve'. Also: when a project loads and has exactly one node (the root) in 'pending' state, auto-select it. The useTree fetchTree returns nodes — after fetch, if selectedNodeId is null and there is a root node that is pending, auto-select it.","also_investigate":"Check if the decomposition actually runs end-to-end. The approve endpoint at src/server/routes/nodes.ts line 176 calls decomposeNode(node.id) in background. The decomposeNode function calls Claude API. Verify ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is available (check process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY). If the API key might not be set, the decomposition will silently fail — add better error handling that broadcasts the error back to the client via SSE so the user sees it."},"issue_3_ato_title":{"problem":"The sidebar header shows '🌳 ATO' (App.tsx line 125). The Crown does not know what ATO stands for.","fix":"Change the title to '🌳 Agent Tree Orchestrator'. If space is tight in the narrow sidebar, use '🌳 Agent Tree Orch.' or add a full title as a tooltip/title attribute. The browser tab title (index.html or vite config) should also be updated to 'Agent Tree Orchestrator' if it currently says 'ATO'."},"issue_4_playwright_tests":{"problem":"The existing tests in tests/e2e/smoke.spec.js are minimal smoke tests. The Crown wants comprehensive Playwright CLI tests that cover the entire workflow.","fix":"Create a new test file at tests/e2e/workflow.spec.js that covers the full tree-building workflow using Playwright CLI (npx playwright test — no MCP). Tests should: (1) load the app, (2) create a new project via the dialog, (3) verify the root node appears and is auto-selected in pending state, (4) click Approve & Decompose on the root node, (5) wait for decomposition status (decomposing → approved with children), (6) verify child nodes appear in the tree graph, (7) select a child node and verify its detail panel, (8) test editing a node's prompt, (9) take screenshots at key stages using page.screenshot() and save them LOCALLY to tests/screenshots/ directory (NOT via MCP). Use page.screenshot({ path: 'tests/screenshots/step-N-description.png' }) for each key step. For decomposition tests: since the actual Claude API call takes time, either (a) mock the API response using Playwright route interception (page.route('/api/nodes/*/approve', ...)) to immediately return success and simulate a node:created SSE event, OR (b) set a generous timeout (120 seconds) for decomposition to complete. Prefer mocking for speed. The config at playwright.config.js already sets baseURL to http://localhost:3000. Add a webServer config to playwright.config.js to start the app automatically: { command: 'npm run dev', port: 3000, reuseExistingServer: true }. Also make sure the tests/screenshots/ directory exists (add .gitkeep). Run the tests with: cd /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator && npx playwright test tests/e2e/workflow.spec.js --reporter=line to verify they pass.","additional_test_tools":"The existing package.json already has @playwright/test. Check if playwright browsers are installed with: npx playwright install chromium. The app serves frontend on port 3000 and API on port 3001 — the vite config proxies /api to 3001. Screenshot assertions and visual regression are NOT needed — just functional tests with screenshots for documentation."}},"acceptance_criteria":["Project creation dialog has NO system prompt field — only name and description","Description is passed as root node prompt so decomposition has context","After project creation, root node is auto-selected and NodeDetail shows Approve & Decompose button","Sidebar title reads 'Agent Tree Orchestrator' (not 'ATO')","Browser tab title updated to 'Agent Tree Orchestrator'","Playwright workflow tests exist at tests/e2e/workflow.spec.js","Tests cover: app load, project create, node auto-select, approve flow, child nodes appearing","Tests take screenshots locally to tests/screenshots/","npx playwright test runs without fatal errors","All changes committed and pushed to git"],"key_files":["/scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/client/App.tsx","/scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/client/hooks/useTree.ts","/scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/server/routes/nodes.ts","/scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/server/services/decomposition.ts","/scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/playwright.config.js","/scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/tests/e2e/smoke.spec.js","/scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/index.html"],"technical_notes":["Work in /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/ — this is the git repo","Frontend: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite on port 3000","Backend: Express on port 3001, SQLite via better-sqlite3","Real-time updates via SSE at /api/events","After all code changes: git add specific files, git commit with format 'fix: <description>', git push","Use npx playwright test (CLI mode) for testing — zero MCP tokens","Screenshots go to tests/screenshots/ locally, never sent through MCP","To build: npm run build in the repo. To check types: npx tsc --noEmit"]},"callback_subject":"raven.chancellor.response"},"ts":"2026-03-15T06:15:14.315Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"request_id":"req-orchestrator-fixes-002","from":"chancellor","to":"forge","action":"build","priority":"normal","payload":{"description":"Fix 4 issues in the Forge orchestrator app and add Playwright CLI tests","context":"The orchestrator app is running but has bugs. Crown has reviewed and identified these specific issues to fix. A previous dispatch failed — this is a retry with clearer instructions.","acceptance_criteria":["1. REMOVE system prompt field from new-project dialog. The CLAUDE.md should NOT be collected at project creation. Instead, it should be auto-generated by Claude Code only after the entire tree is built and approved, then displayed read-only to the user.","2. FIX initial node stuck on pending. When a new project is created, the root node should immediately begin decomposing (not stay in pending state forever). Investigate the decomposition trigger — likely a missing API call, event dispatch, or worker not starting.","3. RENAME/CLARIFY the ATO title. Find where ATO appears in the UI and replace it with a clear descriptive name (e.g. Project Orchestrator, Task Tree Builder, or whatever fits the app purpose). If ATO is an acronym with meaning, keep it but add the full name as a subtitle or tooltip.","4. PLAYWRIGHT CLI TESTS: Write end-to-end tests using Playwright CLI (npx playwright test — zero MCP, CLI only). Tests should cover the full workflow: (a) open app, (b) create new project, (c) verify root node appears and begins decomposing, (d) wait for child nodes to appear, (e) approve/interact with nodes as needed, (f) verify tree is built out, (g) verify CLAUDE.md is auto-generated and visible at end. Take screenshots at key steps using page.screenshot() saving to /tmp/orchestrator-test-screenshots/. View screenshots locally — do NOT send through MCP.","5. Report any Playwright test tools or browser deps that are missing and would be helpful for testing."],"notes":"Find the orchestrator app code in the kingdom-forge repo (check /scrolls/kingdom-forge/ or the GitHub repo HandelSim/kingdom-forge). Read the existing code thoroughly before making changes. Use Edit not Write for modifications. One commit per fix. Run playwright tests with: npx playwright test --reporter=line"},"callback_subject":"raven.chancellor.response"},"ts":"2026-03-15T06:51:59.826Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"request_id":"req-orchestrator-v3-001","from":"chancellor","to":"forge","action":"build","priority":"normal","payload":{"description":"Fix and enhance the Agent Tree Orchestrator app at /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator. Here are the required changes:\n\n1. STATUS LABEL: In src/client/components/StatusBadge.tsx line 14, change the 'pending' label from 'Pending' to 'Awaiting Approval'.\n\n2. PROJECT CREATION - REMOVE SYSTEM PROMPT FIELD: In src/client/App.tsx, remove the 'System Prompt / Spec' textarea from the CreateProjectModal. The modal should only collect: Project Name (required) and Project Goal/Description (required, with placeholder text like 'Be as descriptive as possible — include tech stack, constraints, and end goals. The more detail you provide, the better Claude can plan.'). Update handleCreateProject to only pass name and description.\n\n3. AUTO-GENERATE INITIAL NODE WITH CLAUDE CODE PLAN MODE: After a project is created, the server should automatically call Claude Code in plan mode (claude --plan-mode -p) to generate all the arguments for the initial root node. Create a new server service at src/server/services/initial-node-generator.ts. This service takes project name and description, runs: `claude --plan-mode -p \"You are planning a software project. Given the project name and description, generate a detailed root node configuration as JSON with fields: name (project root name), prompt (comprehensive task prompt), role (appropriate role), is_leaf (always false for root), model (sonnet/haiku/opus), acceptance_criteria, allowed_tools array, max_iterations (number), escalation_policy.\\n\\nProject Name: {name}\\nProject Description: {description}\\n\\nRespond with ONLY valid JSON.\"` and uses the output to update the root node. The node should remain status='pending' (Awaiting Approval) but be populated with generated values. If claude CLI is not available, fall back to using the Anthropic SDK directly.\n\n4. MANUAL/AUTOMATIC MODE: Add a project-level mode setting. Add a 'mode' column to the projects table (TEXT DEFAULT 'manual'). In the UI, add a toggle in the toolbar (when a project is selected) showing 'Manual' | 'Auto' mode. In manual mode: nodes stay 'Awaiting Approval' until user approves them. In automatic mode: after decomposition creates child nodes, they are automatically approved and decomposed recursively (if they are orchestrator/non-leaf type). Wire this into the approveNode server endpoint — after creating children in auto mode, immediately queue them for approval/decomposition.\n\n5. APPROVE AS LEAF CHECKBOX: In src/client/components/NodeDetail.tsx, remove the '✓ Approve as Leaf' button (lines 169-176). Instead add a 'is_leaf' checkbox in the config section (src/client/components/ConfigAccordion.tsx) that the user can toggle. The 'Approve & Decompose' button should check this flag — if is_leaf is true, approve without decomposing; if false, decompose. The is_leaf flag should also be generated by Claude in the initial node generation (item 3) and in decomposition.\n\n6. INITIAL NODE LABEL: In src/client/components/StatusBadge.tsx, the TypeBadge shows 'Orchestrator' for the root node's type. Change the TYPE_CONFIG label for 'orchestrator' from 'Orchestrator' to 'Composite' so it does not say 'Orchestrator' on nodes.\n\n7. DESCRIPTION PROMPT TEXT: Already covered in item 2 above — update the description field placeholder to emphasize being descriptive.\n\n8. PLAYWRIGHT TESTS: Write Playwright CLI tests at tests/orchestrator.spec.ts that test the full workflow: (a) Create a new project, (b) Wait for initial node to be auto-generated and show 'Awaiting Approval', (c) In manual mode, approve the root node and verify decomposition starts, (d) Take screenshots at each step using page.screenshot({ path: 'tests/screenshots/step-N.png' }). Run tests with: cd /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator && npx playwright test --reporter=line. Configure playwright.config.js to use the running app at http://localhost:3000 (or whatever port it runs on — check the server config). If the app is not running, start it first with npm run dev in background.\n\nIMPORTANT IMPLEMENTATION NOTES:\n- Read each file before editing it\n- For the Claude Code plan mode integration: run `claude --help` first to check available flags. Use `--print` or `-p` for non-interactive mode. Use `--plan-mode` to enable plan mode.\n- Commit each logical change separately: 'fix: rename pending to awaiting approval', 'feat: auto-generate initial node with claude plan mode', etc.\n- After all changes, run `npm run type-check` in the orchestrator directory to verify no TS errors\n- Take screenshots during playwright tests and save to tests/screenshots/ directory\n- Do NOT use MCP for screenshots — save them as files and verify locally with the Read tool","context":"This is the Agent Tree Orchestrator app (ATO) used by the Forge. The Crown identified 8 issues in the current implementation. The app is a React+TypeScript frontend with an Express backend. Key files: src/client/App.tsx (project creation modal), src/client/components/NodeDetail.tsx (approve buttons), src/client/components/StatusBadge.tsx (status/type labels), src/server/services/decomposition.ts (Claude API decomposition), src/client/types/index.ts (type definitions). The app is at /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/.","acceptance_criteria":["'Pending' label replaced with 'Awaiting Approval' everywhere","Project creation modal only asks for name and description (no system prompt field)","Description field has placeholder emphasizing being descriptive","Claude Code plan mode auto-generates initial node args on project creation","Manual/Auto mode toggle exists and works (auto mode auto-approves generated nodes)","'Approve as Leaf' button removed; is_leaf is a checkbox in config","TypeBadge shows 'Composite' instead of 'Orchestrator'","Playwright tests pass and screenshots are saved to tests/screenshots/","No TypeScript errors after changes"]},"callback_subject":"raven.chancellor.response"},"ts":"2026-03-15T07:31:48.544Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"request_id":"1773589051634-xvfub1","from":"chancellor","to":"forge","action":"continue","priority":"normal","payload":{"description":"Continue work on the software dev orchestrator. Before beginning, pull the latest changes from the remote (git pull) to ensure you are up to date.","context":"Crown directive — continue existing orchestrator work. Sync with remote first.","acceptance_criteria":["Pulled latest from remote before starting","Continued progress on the software dev orchestrator"]},"callback_subject":"raven.chancellor.response"},"ts":"2026-03-15T15:37:40.907Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"Continue and complete the remaining Agent Tree Orchestrator (kingdom-forge-orchestrator) fixes. Git pull first to get latest changes.\n\nALREADY COMPLETED (do NOT redo):\n1. Status label: pending → Awaiting Approval (done in StatusBadge.tsx)\n2. System prompt field removed from project dialog (done in App.tsx)\n3. Auto-select root node after creation (pendingNodeSelect state + useEffect in App.tsx)\n4. Header renamed ATO → Agent Tree Orchestrator\n5. Approve buttons merged into one adaptive button (NodeDetail.tsx)\n6. TypeBadge: Orchestrator → Composite\n7. Basic Playwright tests (5 tests at tests/e2e/workflow.spec.js, all passing)\n\nREMAINING WORK:\n\nA) is_leaf CHECKBOX IN CONFIG (partial - the merge was done but checkbox not added):\n   - In src/client/components/ConfigAccordion.tsx, add an is_leaf boolean toggle/checkbox in the config section\n   - The NodeDetail.tsx approve button already uses node.node_type !== leaf logic; wire the checkbox to update is_leaf on the node\n   - Make sure editing the is_leaf toggle in ConfigAccordion calls onUpdate({ is_leaf: true/false })\n\nB) AUTO-GENERATE INITIAL NODE WITH CLAUDE CODE (if feasible without API key):\n   - Create src/server/services/initial-node-generator.ts\n   - On project creation, call claude -p with the project name+description to generate root node fields (name, prompt, role, acceptance_criteria) as JSON\n   - Update the root node record with the generated fields\n   - If claude CLI is unavailable, skip this and note it in your response\n   - The root node should remain status=pending (Awaiting Approval)\n\nC) MANUAL/AUTO MODE TOGGLE:\n   - Add mode column to projects table: ALTER TABLE projects ADD COLUMN mode TEXT DEFAULT manual\n   - In App.tsx toolbar, add a Manual | Auto toggle button when a project is selected\n   - In auto mode: after decomposition creates child nodes, auto-approve and decompose them recursively\n   - Wire into the server-side approve endpoint (src/server/routes/nodes.ts)\n\nKey files:\n  /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/client/App.tsx\n  /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/client/components/NodeDetail.tsx\n  /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/client/components/ConfigAccordion.tsx\n  /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/server/routes/nodes.ts\n  /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/src/server/routes/projects.ts\n\nAfter each change: git add specific files, git commit with type: description format, git push\nWork in /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/","from":"architect","request_id":"req-orchestrator-resume-001","timestamp":"2026-03-15T16:15:40Z"},"ts":"2026-03-15T16:15:40.933Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"Continue and complete the remaining Agent Tree Orchestrator (kingdom-forge-orchestrator) fixes at /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/. Git pull first.\n\nALREADY COMPLETED — do NOT redo:\n1. Status label: pending → Awaiting Approval (StatusBadge.tsx)\n2. System prompt field removed from project dialog (App.tsx)\n3. Auto-select root node after creation (pendingNodeSelect in App.tsx)\n4. Header renamed: ATO → Agent Tree Orchestrator\n5. Approve buttons merged into one adaptive button (NodeDetail.tsx)\n6. TypeBadge: Orchestrator → Composite\n7. Basic Playwright tests (5 tests passing at tests/e2e/workflow.spec.js)\n\nREMAINING WORK:\n\nA) is_leaf CHECKBOX IN CONFIG:\n   - In src/client/components/ConfigAccordion.tsx, add a is_leaf boolean checkbox toggle\n   - The NodeDetail approve button already reads node.node_type; wire checkbox to call onUpdate({ is_leaf: value }) when editing\n   - Check what fields ConfigAccordion currently renders for context\n\nB) AUTO-GENERATE INITIAL NODE (only if claude CLI is working):\n   - Run: claude --version to check availability\n   - If available: create src/server/services/initial-node-generator.ts\n   - Service takes project name+description, calls claude -p to generate root node JSON (name, prompt, role), updates the root node after project creation\n   - If unavailable: skip this item and note it\n\nC) MANUAL/AUTO MODE TOGGLE:\n   - Add mode column to projects table (see src/server/db.ts or wherever schema is)\n   - Add Manual | Auto toggle button in the App.tsx toolbar\n   - In auto mode: after decomposition creates child nodes, auto-approve them\n   - Wire into server approve endpoint (src/server/routes/nodes.ts)\n\nAfter each change: git add specific files, git commit, git push from /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/","from":"architect","request_id":"req-orchestrator-resume-002","timestamp":"2026-03-15T16:29:38Z"},"ts":"2026-03-15T16:29:38.799Z"}
