8.496Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"Improve the Agent Tree Orchestrator (ATO) codebase with 6 improvements as specified in the attached design document. Full spec is at /tmp/kingdom-uploads/ato-v3-token-efficiency-and-contracts.md — read it entirely before starting.\n\nImplement in this order (each must leave the app working before proceeding):\n\n1. **Improvement 2 first**: Add project lifecycle phases (building → tree_approved → contexts_generating → contexts_generated → executing → completed/failed). Add `status` column to projects table. Add POST /api/project/:id/generate-contexts and POST /api/project/:id/start-execution routes. Add phase-aware action bar to UI.\n\n2. **Improvement 3**: API contract generation. Add `contracts` table, `contract-generator.ts` service, contract agent prompt, write contracts/ directory output, add `apis_provided`/`apis_consumed` columns to nodes, add Contract Registry UI view.\n\n3. **Improvement 5**: CLAUDE.md hierarchy. Implement `generateProjectClaude()`, `generateNodeClaude()`, and `generateSettings()` functions in `context-generator.ts`. Wire into generate-contexts endpoint.\n\n4. **Improvement 1**: Tiered testing. Add `TestingTier` enum and `TierConfig` interface in `src/server/config/testing-tiers.ts`. Add `testing_tier` column to nodes. Create `scripts/capture-screenshots.sh` and `scripts/playwright-cli-check.sh`. Add Testing Tier selector to node config UI.\n\n5. **Improvement 4**: Contract change propagation. Add `contract_change_proposals` table. Create `scripts/contract-guard.py` PreToolUse hook. Add file watcher for `.contract-proposals/`. Implement auto-approve for backward-compatible changes and human-review flow for breaking changes. Add Contract Changes panel to UI.\n\n6. **Improvement 6**: Integration verification. Add sibling-completion check in execution queue. Create `src/server/services/integration-verifier.ts`. Wire Playwright MCP only at Tier 3. Add integration verification status/results to parent node UI.\n\nAll database migrations via SQL ALTER/CREATE TABLE statements. TypeScript strict mode. Read the full spec at /tmp/kingdom-uploads/ato-v3-token-efficiency-and-contracts.md for exact interface definitions, SQL schemas, script contents, and UI requirements.","from":"chancellor","request_id":"1773600034330-2dzn3y","timestamp":"2026-03-15T18:41:01.801Z"},"ts":"2026-03-15T18:41:02.077Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"Get the Agent Tree Orchestrator running for Crown testing. The /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/ has a complete build but node_modules are not installed. From your container (where /scrolls is writable), please: 1) Run `npm install` in /scrolls/kingdom-forge-orchestrator/, 2) Run the build (`npm run build`), 3) Start the dev server (`npm run dev`) or production server (`npm start`) so it's accessible for testing, 4) Report back the URL/port where it's running. The code is up to date with all 6 improvements already committed. request_id: 1773604695018-5h68fw","from":"chancellor","request_id":"1773604695018-5h68fw","timestamp":"2026-03-15T19:59:13.170Z"},"ts":"2026-03-15T19:59:13.218Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"Execute the attached directive exactly as specified. Full instructions:\n\n# FORGE TASK: Rename FIN → SCHEMA, Create HAMMER, Push Both\n\n## Task 1: Rename FIN → SCHEMA\n1a. Find the existing FIN project directory (likely /scrolls/kingdom-fin or similar). Find and replace every occurrence of FIN/fin/Federated Implementation Network across all files with SCHEMA/schema/Self-Constructing Hierarchy for Entire Managed Applications. Rename directory to schema/ if needed. Update git remote: `gh repo rename schema 2>/dev/null || true`\n1b. Update README header as specified.\n1c. Commit: `git commit -m \"Rename FIN → SCHEMA (Self-Constructing Hierarchy for Entire Managed Applications)\"` and push.\n\n## Task 2: Create the HAMMER Repository\nCreate hammer/ as a sibling directory. Initialize as new git repo. Implement ALL files exactly as specified:\n- package.json, tsconfig.json, .gitignore\n- src/types.ts — full HammerConfig, HammerResult, all interfaces\n- src/detect/defaults.ts — resolveConfig with smart defaults, DEFAULT_SUBAGENTS (test-writer + code-reviewer)\n- src/detect/acceptance.ts — autoDetectAcceptanceChecks (TS, Node, ESLint, Python, Go, Rust)\n- src/index.ts — runHammer() export\n- src/cli.ts — full CLI (run, resume, validate, init, templates commands)\n- src/core/executor.ts — main execution loop with retry logic\n- src/core/sdk-wrapper.ts — wrap @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk query()\n- src/core/session.ts — session save/load\n- src/detect/workspace.ts — detect project type/frameworks\n- src/detect/language.ts — detect primary language\n- src/workspace/validator.ts — validateWorkspace()\n- src/workspace/fallback.ts — generateFallbacksIfNeeded()\n- src/workspace/contracts.ts — scan contract files\n- src/testing/acceptance.ts — run acceptance check commands\n- src/testing/screenshots.ts — Playwright screenshot capture\n- src/testing/visual-check.ts — Haiku visual verification\n- src/healing/retry.ts — format failures, build retry prompt\n- src/healing/escalation.ts — handle escalation policies\n- src/utils/cost.ts, logger.ts, events.ts, stdin.ts\n\nCreate scripts/: enforce-boundaries.py, detect-secrets.py, contract-guard.py, tdd-guard.py, save-checkpoint.py, capture-screenshots.sh, playwright-cli-check.sh, check-contract-notifications.sh — each with header comment.\n\nCreate templates/: developer.json, tester.json, visual-qa.json, reviewer.json\n\nCreate README.md with all 12 sections including exact \"For Agents Calling HAMMER\" text.\n\nBuild and push:\n```\nnpm install && npm run build\ngh repo create HandelSim/hammer --private --source=. --push\n```\n\n## Task 3: Wire SCHEMA to Use HAMMER\n1. In SCHEMA: `npm install ../hammer`\n2. Replace execution service with runHammer() calls as specified\n3. Remove code HAMMER now handles: SDK wrapper, retry loop, acceptance checking, screenshots, session mgmt, cost tracking\n4. Ensure Generate Agent Contexts stores HammerConfig JSON on each node\n5. Commit: `git commit -m \"Wire SCHEMA to use HAMMER for node execution\"` and push\n\n## Task 4: Verify\n1. `cd hammer && npm run build` — must succeed\n2. `cd schema && npm run build` — must succeed\n3. `hammer validate --cwd /tmp/test` — smoke test\n\nrequest_id: 1773610053002-lspgjm","from":"chancellor","request_id":"1773610053002-lspgjm","timestamp":"2026-03-15T21:27:58.654Z"},"ts":"2026-03-15T21:27:58.741Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"Use HAMMER to test and fix the SCHEMA web app. The issue: when a user selects a node in the SCHEMA web UI, the page that should appear is rendering all white, and there are errors showing. Steps: (1) Reproduce the white-page/error on node selection, (2) identify the root cause (likely a React component crash, missing error boundary, or broken route/prop), (3) fix it, (4) verify the node detail page renders correctly after selection. Repo: HandelSim/schema. Use HAMMER for the build/fix cycle. request_id: 1773614562027-svn9ay","from":"chancellor","request_id":"1773614562027-svn9ay","timestamp":"2026-03-15T22:42:53.398Z"},"ts":"2026-03-15T22:42:53.445Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"request_id":"req-hammer-browser-tools-1773615620874","from":"architect","to":"forge","action":"update_hammer","priority":"normal","payload":{"description":"Integrate tiered browser debugging tools into HAMMER","context":"The Forge container image has been rebuilt with new browser tools. The tools manifest is at /home/claude/.forge-tools-manifest.json. Read it first to understand what is installed.\n\nIMPORTANT: After the Crown rebuilds the container (docker compose build the-forge && docker compose up -d the-forge), the following tools will be available globally:\n- agent-browser (Vercel Rust CLI, npm install -g agent-browser)\n- playwright-cli (Microsoft, npm install -g @playwright/cli)\n- Context7 MCP (npx-invocable, already in /workspace/.mcp.json)\n- Chrome DevTools MCP (npx-invocable, HAMMER enables on-demand)","acceptance_criteria":["Create src/detect/browser-tools.ts with detectBrowserTools() function that checks for agent-browser and playwright-cli binaries and reads the manifest","Update src/workspace/fallback.ts to append browser tools documentation to generated CLAUDE.md content","Update src/testing/screenshots.ts to prefer agent-browser > playwright-cli > npx playwright (tiered fallback)","Add classifyFailure() and escalation logic in src/core/executor.ts to auto-enable Chrome DevTools MCP when browser issues detected on retry","Add Browser Debugging Tools section to HAMMER README.md documenting the three tiers","Add browser tools section to Forge CLAUDE.md","Commit and push all changes: git commit -m \"feat: integrate tiered browser debugging tools (agent-browser, playwright-cli, context7, devtools)\""]},"callback_subject":"raven.architect.response"},"ts":"2026-03-15T23:00:21.041Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"Use HAMMER with Chrome DevTools (agent-browser CLI or Playwright) to test the SCHEMA app and identify broken requests. Steps: 1) Launch the SCHEMA app locally or connect to its deployed instance, 2) Use browser devtools / network inspection to capture all HTTP requests and identify which are failing (4xx, 5xx, CORS errors, etc.), 3) Document each broken request: endpoint, method, status code, error message, 4) Attempt to fix any broken requests you can identify in the codebase, 5) Report a full summary of findings and any fixes applied. Use the HAMMER tool (`hammer run`) for any code fixes needed. Repo: https://github.com/HandelSim/schema","from":"chancellor","request_id":"1773616408531-u2r0wd","timestamp":"2026-03-15T23:13:37.200Z"},"ts":"2026-03-15T23:13:37.246Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"Investigate why the SCHEMA app generates requests at an excessively fast rate. Clone/examine the SCHEMA repo at https://github.com/HandelSim/schema. Find the root cause — likely a polling loop, retry logic, or agent coordination cycle with no delay/backoff. Assess whether slowing the request rate (via throttling, debouncing, sleep intervals, or exponential backoff) would affect functionality. If safe to do so, implement a conservative rate limit or delay. Report findings and any changes made. request_id: 1773618517849-kq5svi","from":"chancellor","request_id":"1773618517849-kq5svi","timestamp":"2026-03-15T23:48:50.704Z"},"ts":"2026-03-15T23:48:50.747Z"}
{"subject":"raven.forge.assigned","data":{"task":"The SCHEMA app is generating 10+ requests per second, bogging down the Crown's computer. Investigate the source of this high-frequency request pattern in the SCHEMA codebase (https://github.com/HandelSim/schema). Look for polling loops, unbounded event listeners, or missing debounce/throttle logic. Fix the root cause — add rate limiting, backoff, or replace polling with event-driven patterns where appropriate. The goal is to reduce requests to a reasonable rate (ideally event-driven with no busy-polling).","from":"chancellor","request_id":"1773619868306-ux1qp3","timestamp":"2026-03-16T00:11:20.006Z"},"ts":"2026-03-16T00:11:20.050Z"}
